I guess we have to
talk about green beer.

00:27:33.830 --> 00:27:35.720
So let's talk about
alcohol for a second.

00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:39.590
So it turns out that your liver
produces this thing called

00:27:39.590 --> 00:27:41.540
alcohol dehydrogenase.

00:27:41.540 --> 00:27:43.880
And what it does is it
actually helps filter

00:27:43.880 --> 00:27:47.360
through and get that
alcohol out of your system.

00:27:47.360 --> 00:27:48.180
Guess what.

00:27:48.180 --> 00:27:51.080
It doesn't really happen
very much in the mornings.

00:27:51.080 --> 00:27:55.100
So if you're having brunch
and having mimosas and Bloody

00:27:55.100 --> 00:27:57.560
Marys, you really need
about half the amount

00:27:57.560 --> 00:27:59.450
of alcohol in the
morning that you

00:27:59.450 --> 00:28:02.690
would normally to get the
same effect in the afternoon

00:28:02.690 --> 00:28:03.770
or evening.

00:28:03.770 --> 00:28:06.740
So that's kind of interesting in
terms of your tolerance rhythm

00:28:06.740 --> 00:28:07.550
will change.

00:28:07.550 --> 00:28:09.200
You are much less tolerant.

00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:11.750
Alcohol has a much bigger
effect on you in the mornings

00:28:11.750 --> 00:28:13.790
than it ever will in the
afternoons or evenings.

00:28:13.790 --> 00:28:16.070
But then there's this
thing called happy hour.

00:28:16.070 --> 00:28:17.480
And so what is happy hour?

00:28:17.480 --> 00:28:19.130
Happy hour is
really interesting,

00:28:19.130 --> 00:28:22.840
because when you look at it
from a biochemical standpoint,

00:28:22.840 --> 00:28:24.770
this alcohol
dehydrogenase really

00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:27.980
kicks into gear
about 4:30, 5:00,

00:28:27.980 --> 00:28:30.860
and it goes really
hard until about 7:00.

00:28:30.860 --> 00:28:32.750
So a lot of the
alcohol establishments

00:28:32.750 --> 00:28:35.810
over the last 100 years or
so had figured out this,

00:28:35.810 --> 00:28:38.030
and they know that you'll
actually be drinking more

00:28:38.030 --> 00:28:39.155
during this period of time.

00:28:39.155 --> 00:28:41.570
And that's why they give you
free food or reduced cost

00:28:41.570 --> 00:28:43.370
food to drive you in
to then drink more,

00:28:43.370 --> 00:28:46.550
because your body can
actually handle drinking more

00:28:46.550 --> 00:28:47.270
at that point.

00:28:47.270 --> 00:28:49.710
Now what ends up
happening is sometimes

00:28:49.710 --> 00:28:51.380
you may drink in a
little bit of excess,

00:28:51.380 --> 00:28:53.090
and then you end
up with a hangover.

00:28:53.090 --> 00:28:55.340
So there's something
called the hangover rhythm.

00:28:55.340 --> 00:28:57.290
And so this is
actually, again, when

00:28:57.290 --> 00:29:00.019
is your body able to pull
the alcohol in or out.

00:29:00.019 --> 00:29:02.060
And when you take all
these rhythms into account,

00:29:02.060 --> 00:29:03.976
there's a couple of
things that you can learn.

00:29:03.976 --> 00:29:06.890
So this is what I call
strategic drinking.

00:29:06.890 --> 00:29:09.950
So if you go by your
chronotype, here's

00:29:09.950 --> 00:29:12.800
what you will learn is
that dolphins are actually

00:29:12.800 --> 00:29:14.440
good between 6:00 and 8:00.

00:29:14.440 --> 00:29:16.710
Lions, again, a
little bit earlier.

00:29:16.710 --> 00:29:18.440
Bears-- kind of in the middle.

00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:21.680
And then wolves-- we can
party all night long.

00:29:21.680 --> 00:29:23.390
And so it's kind
of interesting when

00:29:23.390 --> 00:29:25.280
you start to think
through the idea

00:29:25.280 --> 00:29:28.250
of chemically or
biochemically speaking, what's

00:29:28.250 --> 00:29:29.270
going on in your body.

00:29:29.270 --> 00:29:32.240
How could that
possibly have an effect

00:29:32.240 --> 00:29:34.250
on whatever it is
that you're ingesting,

00:29:34.250 --> 00:29:36.602
whether it's caffeine,
alcohol, you name it?

00:29:36.602 --> 00:29:38.810
And then I also brought in
a couple of hangover hacks

00:29:38.810 --> 00:29:40.910
for people who are wolves,
who have a tendency

00:29:40.910 --> 00:29:42.621
to drink late at night.

00:29:42.621 --> 00:29:44.870
A couple of things to think
about-- one glass of water

00:29:44.870 --> 00:29:46.190
for every alcoholic beverage.

00:29:46.190 --> 00:29:48.467
Number one, it slows down
the sheer volume of alcohol

00:29:48.467 --> 00:29:50.300
you're putting in your
system, but remember,

00:29:50.300 --> 00:29:51.561
alcohol is a diuretic.

00:29:51.561 --> 00:29:53.060
And sort of once
you break the seal,

00:29:53.060 --> 00:29:54.830
and you go to the bathroom
once, you're done.

